cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with evaluating the capabilities of computational models for text understanding by means of a word prediction task. It also discusses linguistic phenomena and proposes a challenging test set to encourage the development of new models capable of genuine understanding of broad context in natural language text. 

It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the development and evaluation of language models. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category as the paper deals with the ability of computational models to understand natural language text. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) could also be a possible sub-category as the paper discusses state-of-the-art language models that use neural networks. 

Finally, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) could be a less likely sub-category as the paper mentions the use of natural language text, but does not focus on visual data.
